Manchester United captain Harry Maguire was on Tuesday given a 21-month suspended prison sentence on assault charges by a court in Greece. The England international defender was arrested late Thursday after a fight at a nightclub in Mykonos. He was charged with assault, bodily harm, verbal abuse and attempted bribery. Maguire, who did not attend the hearing on the Greek island of Syros, released a statement saying he intended to appeal the verdict. VANGUARD Harry Maguire is co-operating with Greek authorities following an alleged incident in Mykonos, Manchester United have confirmed. The Red Devils captain has been on holiday on the island after United's 2019-20 season ended with a 2-1 defeat to Sevilla in the Europa League semi-final. ALSO READ: PSG star Verratti desperate to… August 21, 2020 In "Sports" After a chastening few months following Ole Gunnar Solskjaer's appointment on a permanent basis as Manchester United manager, there is cause for optimism again at Old Trafford after romping to a 4-0 win over Chelsea on the opening weekend of the Premier League season. August 11, 2019 In "News" Manchester United made Harry Maguire the world's most expensive defender on Monday as they bought the England centre-back from Leicester for a reported fee of £80 million ($97 million). August 5, 2019 In "News"